105 #define ELAPSED_MSECS(e, s) \
106  ((e).tv_sec - (s).tv_sec) * 1000 + ((e).tv_usec - (s).tv_usec) / 1000
107 
108 #define IS_OUT_TRAN_STATUS(CON_HANDLE) \
109  (IS_INVALID_SOCKET((CON_HANDLE)->sock_fd) || \
110  ((CON_HANDLE)->con_status == CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN))
111 
112 #define IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL(c) \
113  ((c)->broker_info[BROKER_INFO_STATEMENT_POOLING] == CAS_STATEMENT_POOLING_ON)
114 #define IS_OUT_TRAN(c) ((c)->con_status == CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN)
115 #define IS_IN_TRAN(c) ((c)->con_status == CCI_CON_STATUS_IN_TRAN)
116 #define IS_FORCE_FAILBACK(c) ((c)->force_failback == 1)
117 #define IS_ER_COMMUNICATION(e) \
118  ((e) == CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION || (e) == CAS_ER_COMMUNICATION)
119 #define IS_SERVER_DOWN(e) \
120  (((e) == ER_TM_SERVER_DOWN_UNILATERALLY_ABORTED) \
121  || ((e) == ER_OBJ_NO_CONNECT) || ((e) == ER_NET_SERVER_CRASHED) \
122  || ((e) == ER_BO_CONNECT_FAILED))
123 #define IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT(e1, e2) \
124  (((e1) == CCI_ER_DBMS && IS_SERVER_DOWN (e2)) ? true : IS_ER_COMMUNICATION (e1))
125 
126 #define NEED_TO_RECONNECT(CON,ERR) \
127  (IS_ER_COMMUNICATION(ERR) || !hm_broker_reconnect_when_server_down(CON))
128 
129 /* default value of each datesource property */
130 #define CCI_DS_POOL_SIZE_DEFAULT 10
131 #define CCI_DS_MAX_WAIT_DEFAULT 1000
132 #define CCI_DS_POOL_PREPARED_STATEMENT_DEFAULT false
133 #define CCI_DS_MAX_OPEN_PREPARED_STATEMENT_DEFAULT 1000
134 #define CCI_DS_DISCONNECT_ON_QUERY_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT false
135 #define CCI_DS_DEFAULT_AUTOCOMMIT_DEFAULT (CCI_AUTOCOMMIT_TRUE)
136 #define CCI_DS_DEFAULT_ISOLATION_DEFAULT TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION
137 #define CCI_DS_DEFAULT_LOCK_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT CCI_LOCK_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT
138 #define CCI_DS_LOGIN_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT (CCI_LOGIN_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT)
139

141 #define CON_ID(a) ((a) / CON_HANDLE_ID_FACTOR)

268 int
269 get_elapsed_time (struct timeval *start_time)
270 {
271  INT64 start_time_milli, end_time_milli;
272  struct timeval end_time;
273 
274  assert (start_time);
275 
276  if (start_time->tv_sec == 0 && start_time->tv_usec == 0)
277  {
278  return 0;
279  }
280 
281  gettimeofday (&end_time, NULL);
282 
283  start_time_milli = start_time->tv_sec * 1000LL + start_time->tv_usec / 1000LL;
284  end_time_milli = end_time.tv_sec * 1000LL + end_time.tv_usec / 1000LL;
285 
286  return (int) (end_time_milli - start_time_milli);
287 }

289 void
290 cci_init ()
291 {
292 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
293  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_init"));
294 #endif
295 
296  if (cci_init_flag)
297  {
298  cci_init_flag = 0;
299 #if defined(WINDOWS)
300  MUTEX_INIT (con_handle_table_mutex);
301 #endif
302  }
303 }
304 
305 void
306 cci_end (void)
307 {
308  return;
309 }

321 int
322 cci_get_version (int *major, int *minor, int *patch)
323 {
324 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
325  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_get_version:%d.%d.%d", MAJOR_VERSION, MINOR_VERSION, PATCH_VERSION));
326 #endif
327 
328  if (major)
329  {
330  *major = MAJOR_VERSION;
331  }
332  if (minor)
333  {
334  *minor = MINOR_VERSION;
335  }
336  if (patch)
337  {
338  *patch = PATCH_VERSION;
339  }
340  return 0;
341 }

343 static int
344 cci_connect_internal (char *ip, int port, char *db, char *user, char *pass, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
345 {
346  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle;
347  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
348 
349  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
350 
351  if (ip == NULL || port < 0 || db == NULL || user == NULL || pass == NULL)
352  {
353  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
354  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
355  }
356 
357 #if defined(WINDOWS)
358  if (wsa_initialize () < 0)
359  {
360  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
361  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
362  }
363 #endif
364 
365  con_handle = get_new_connection (ip, port, db, user, pass);
366  if (con_handle == NULL)
367  {
368  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
369 
370  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
371  }
372 
373  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
374 
375  SET_START_TIME_FOR_LOGIN (con_handle);
376  error = cas_connect (con_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
377  if (error < 0)
378  {
379  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
380  hm_con_handle_free (con_handle);
381  goto error;
382  }
383 
384  error = qe_end_tran (con_handle, CCI_TRAN_COMMIT, &con_handle->err_buf);
385  if (error < 0)
386  {
387  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
388  hm_con_handle_free (con_handle);
389  goto error;
390  }
391 
392  SET_AUTOCOMMIT_FROM_CASINFO (con_handle);
393  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
394 
395  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
396  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
397 
398  return con_handle->id;
399 
400 error:
401 
402  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
403 
404  return error;
405 }
406 
407 int
408 cci_connect_ex (char *ip, int port, char *db, char *user, char *pass, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
409 {
410  T_CCI_CONN connection_id, mapped_conn_id;
411 
412  connection_id = cci_connect_internal (ip, port, db, user, pass, err_buf);
413  if (connection_id < 0)
414  {
415  return connection_id;
416  }
417 
418  map_open_otc (connection_id, &mapped_conn_id);
419  return mapped_conn_id;
420 }

422 int
423 CCI_CONNECT_INTERNAL_FUNC_NAME (char *ip, int port, char *db_name, char *db_user, char *dbpasswd)
424 {
425  T_CCI_CONN connection_id, mapped_conn_id;
426 
427  connection_id = cci_connect_internal (ip, port, db_name, db_user, dbpasswd, NULL);
428 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
429  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
430  ("cci_connect (pid %d, h:%d): %s %d %s %s %s", getpid (), connection_id, ip, port,
431  DEBUG_STR (db_name), DEBUG_STR (db_user), DEBUG_STR (dbpasswd)));
432 #endif
433  if (connection_id < 0)
434  {
435  return connection_id;
436  }
437 
438  map_open_otc (connection_id, &mapped_conn_id);
439  return mapped_conn_id;
440 }

442 static int
443 cci_connect_with_url_internal (char *url, char *user, char *pass, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
444 {
445  char *token[MAX_URL_MATCH_COUNT] = { NULL };
446  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
447  unsigned i;
448 
449  char *property = NULL;
450  char *end = NULL;
451  char *host, *dbname;
452  int port;
453  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
454 
455  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
456 
457 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
458  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
459  ("cci_connect_with_url %s %s %s", DEBUG_STR (url), DEBUG_STR (user), DEBUG_STR (pass)));
460 #endif
461 
462  if (url == NULL)
463  {
464  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
465  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
466  }
467 
468 #if defined(WINDOWS)
469  if (wsa_initialize () < 0)
470  {
471  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
472  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
473  }
474 #endif
475 
476  error = cci_url_match (url, token);
477  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
478  {
479  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
480  return error;
481  }
482 
483  host = token[0];
484  port = (int) strtol (token[1], &end, 10);
485  dbname = token[2];
486 
487  if (user == NULL)
488  {
489  user = token[3];
490  }
491  if (pass == NULL)
492  {
493  pass = token[4];
494  }
495 
496  property = token[5];
497  if (property == NULL)
498  {
499  property = (char *) "";
500  }
501 
502  /* start health check thread */
503  MUTEX_LOCK (health_check_th_mutex);
504  if (!is_health_check_th_started)
505  {
506  hm_create_health_check_th ();
507  is_health_check_th_started = 1;
508  }
509  MUTEX_UNLOCK (health_check_th_mutex);
510 
511  con_handle = get_new_connection (host, port, dbname, user, pass);
512  if (con_handle == NULL)
513  {
514  for (i = 0; i < MAX_URL_MATCH_COUNT; i++)
515  {
516  FREE_MEM (token[i]);
517  }
518 
519  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_CONNECT, NULL);
520  return CCI_ER_CONNECT;
521  }
522 
523  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
524 
525  snprintf (con_handle->url, SRV_CON_URL_SIZE, "cci:cubrid:%s:%d:%s:%s:********:%s", host, port, dbname, user,
526  property);
527 
528  if (property != NULL)
529  {
530  error = cci_conn_set_properties (con_handle, property);
531  API_SLOG (con_handle);
532 
533  if (con_handle->log_trace_api)
534  {
535  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger, "URL[%s]", url);
536  }
537 
538  if (error < 0)
539  {
540  hm_con_handle_free (con_handle);
541  goto ret;
542  }
543 
544  if (con_handle->alter_host_count > 0)
545  {
546  con_handle->alter_host_id = 0;
547  }
548  }
549 
550  SET_START_TIME_FOR_LOGIN (con_handle);
551  error = cas_connect (con_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
552  if (error < 0)
553  {
554  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
555  hm_con_handle_free (con_handle);
556  goto ret;
557  }
558 
559  error = qe_end_tran (con_handle, CCI_TRAN_COMMIT, &con_handle->err_buf);
560  if (error < 0)
561  {
562  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
563  hm_con_handle_free (con_handle);
564  goto ret;
565  }
566 
567  SET_AUTOCOMMIT_FROM_CASINFO (con_handle);
568  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
569 
570 ret:
571  for (i = 0; i < MAX_URL_MATCH_COUNT; i++)
572  {
573  FREE_MEM (token[i]);
574  }
575 
576 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
577  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_connect_with_url return %d", conn_id));
578 #endif
579 
580  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
581  {
582  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
583  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
584  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
585 
586  return con_handle->id;
587  }
588 
589  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
590 
591  return error;
592 }
593 
594 int
595 cci_connect_with_url (char *url, char *user, char *password)
596 {
597  T_CCI_CONN connection_id, mapped_conn_id;
598 
599  connection_id = cci_connect_with_url_internal (url, user, password, NULL);
600  if (connection_id < 0)
601  {
602  return connection_id;
603  }
604 
605  map_open_otc (connection_id, &mapped_conn_id);
606  return mapped_conn_id;
607 }

609 int
610 cci_connect_with_url_ex (char *url, char *user, char *pass, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
611 {
612  T_CCI_CONN connection_id, mapped_conn_id;
613 
614  connection_id = cci_connect_with_url_internal (url, user, pass, err_buf);
615  if (connection_id < 0)
616  {
617  return connection_id;
618  }
619 
620  map_open_otc (connection_id, &mapped_conn_id);
621  return mapped_conn_id;
622 }
623 
624 #if defined UNUSED_FUNCTION
625 static int
626 cas_end_session (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
627 {
628  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
629 
630  API_SLOG (con_handle);
631 
632  error = qe_end_session (con_handle, err_buf);
633  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
634  {
635  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
636  {
637  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
638  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
639  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
640  {
641  break;
642  }
643  }
644 
645 
646  error = qe_end_session (con_handle, err_buf);
647  }
648 
649  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
650  return error;
651 }
652 #endif
653 
654 int
655 cci_disconnect (int mapped_conn_id, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
656 {
657  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
658  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
659 
660 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
661  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)cci_disconnect", mapped_conn_id));
662 #endif
663 
664  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
665  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
666  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
667  {
668  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
669  return error;
670  }
671  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
672  con_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
673 
674  API_SLOG (con_handle);
675 
676  if (con_handle->datasource)
677  {
678  con_handle->used = false;
679  hm_release_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
680 
681  if (cci_end_tran_internal (con_handle, CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK) != NO_ERROR)
682  {
683  qe_con_close (con_handle);
684  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
685  }
686 
687  cci_datasource_release_internal (con_handle->datasource, con_handle);
688  if (con_handle->log_trace_api)
689  {
690  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger, "[%04d][API][E][cci_datasource_release]", con_handle->id);
691  }
692 
693  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
694  }
695  else if (con_handle->broker_info[BROKER_INFO_CCI_PCONNECT] && hm_put_con_to_pool (con_handle->id) >= 0)
696  {
697  cci_end_tran_internal (con_handle, CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK);
698  API_ELOG (con_handle, 0);
699 
700  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
701  con_handle->used = false;
702  hm_release_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
703  }
704  else
705  {
706  error = qe_con_close (con_handle);
707  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
708 
709  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
710  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
711  con_handle->used = false;
712 
713  MUTEX_LOCK (con_handle_table_mutex);
714  hm_delete_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
715  MUTEX_UNLOCK (con_handle_table_mutex);
716  }
717 
718  return error;
719 }
720 
721 int
722 cci_cancel (int mapped_conn_id)
723 {
724  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
725  int error;
726 
727  error = hm_get_connection_force (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
728  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
729  {
730  return error;
731  }
732 
733  API_SLOG (con_handle);
734  error = net_cancel_request (con_handle);
735  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
736 
737  return error;
738 }
739 
740 static int
741 cci_end_tran_internal (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char type)
742 {
743  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
744 
745  if (IS_IN_TRAN (con_handle))
746  {
747  error = qe_end_tran (con_handle, type, &(con_handle->err_buf));
748  }
749  else if (type == CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK)
750  {
751  /* even if con status is CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN, there may be holdable req_handles that remained open after
752  * commit if a rollback is done after commit, these req_handles should be closed or freed */
753  if (con_handle->broker_info[BROKER_INFO_STATEMENT_POOLING] != CAS_STATEMENT_POOLING_ON)
754  {
755  hm_req_handle_free_all (con_handle);
756  }
757  else
758  {
759  hm_req_handle_close_all_resultsets (con_handle);
760  }
761  }
762  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
763 
764  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
765  {
766  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
767  }
768 
769  return error;
770 }
771 
772 int
773 cci_end_tran (int mapped_conn_id, char type, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
774 {
775  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
776  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
777 
778 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
779  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)tran: %s", mapped_conn_id, dbg_tran_type_str (type)));
780 #endif
781 
782  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
783  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
784  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
785  {
786  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
787  return error;
788  }
789 
790  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
791 
792  API_SLOG (con_handle);
793 
794  error = cci_end_tran_internal (con_handle, type);
795 
796  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
797  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
798  con_handle->used = false;
799 
800  return error;
801 }
802 
803 static int
804 reset_connect (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
805 {
806  int connect_done;
807  int error;
808  int old_timeout;
809 
810  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
811  if (req_handle != NULL)
812  {
813  req_handle_content_free (req_handle, 1);
814  }
815 
816  /* save query timeout */
817  old_timeout = con_handle->current_timeout;
818  if (con_handle->current_timeout <= 0)
819  {
820  /* if (query_timeout <= 0) */
821  con_handle->current_timeout = con_handle->login_timeout;
822  }
823  error = cas_connect_with_ret (con_handle, err_buf, &connect_done);
824 
825  /* restore query timeout */
826  con_handle->current_timeout = old_timeout;
827  if (error < 0 || !connect_done)
828  {
829  return error;
830  }
831 
832  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
833 }
834 
835 /*
836  * For the purpose of re-balancing existing connections, cci_prepare,
837  * cci_execute, cci_execute_array, cci_prepare_and_execute,
838  * cci_execute_batch require to forcefully disconnect the current
839  * con_handle when it is in the OUT_TRAN state and the time elapsed
840  * after the last failure of a host is over rc_time.
841  */
842 int
843 cci_prepare (int mapped_conn_id, char *sql_stmt, char flag, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
844 {
845  int statement_id = -1;
846  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
847  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
848  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
849  int is_first_prepare_in_tran;
850 
851  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
852  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
853  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
854  {
855  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
856  return error;
857  }
858  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
859 
860  if (sql_stmt == NULL)
861  {
862  error = CCI_ER_STRING_PARAM;
863  goto error;
864  }
865 
866  API_SLOG (con_handle);
867  if (con_handle->log_trace_api)
868  {
869  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger, "FLAG[%d],SQL[%s]", flag, sql_stmt);
870  }
871 
872  if (DOES_CONNECTION_HAVE_STMT_POOL (con_handle))
873  {
874  statement_id = hm_req_get_from_pool (con_handle, &req_handle, sql_stmt);
875  if (statement_id != CCI_ER_REQ_HANDLE)
876  {
877  req_handle->query_timeout = con_handle->query_timeout;
878  goto prepare_end;
879  }
880  }
881 
882  statement_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
883  if (statement_id < 0)
884  {
885  error = statement_id;
886  goto prepare_error;
887  }
888 
889  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_FORCE_FAILBACK (con_handle) && !IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
890  {
891  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
892  }
893  SET_START_TIME_FOR_QUERY (con_handle, req_handle);
894 
895  is_first_prepare_in_tran = IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle);
896 
897  error = qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, sql_stmt, flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 0);
898 
899  while ((IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) || is_first_prepare_in_tran)
900  && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
901  {
902  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
903  {
904  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
905  error = reset_connect (con_handle, req_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
906  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
907  {
908  break;
909  }
910  }
911 
912  error = qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, sql_stmt, flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 0);
913  }
914 
915  if (error < 0)
916  {
917  goto prepare_error;
918  }
919 
920  if (DOES_CONNECTION_HAVE_STMT_POOL (con_handle))
921  {
922  /* add new allocated req_handle to use list */
923  hm_pool_add_statement_to_use (con_handle, statement_id);
924  }
925 
926 prepare_end:
927  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
928 
929  API_ELOG (con_handle, statement_id);
930 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
931  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
932  ("(%d:%d)pre: %d %s", mapped_conn_id, REQ_ID (statement_id), flag, DEBUG_STR (sql_stmt)));
933 #endif
934 
935  map_open_ots (statement_id, &req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
936  con_handle->used = false;
937 
938  return req_handle->mapped_stmt_id;
939 
940 prepare_error:
941  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
942 
943  if (req_handle)
944  {
945  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
946  req_handle = NULL;
947  }
948 
949  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout)
950  {
951  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
952  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
953  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
954  }
955 
956  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
957  {
958  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
959  }
960 
961 error:
962  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
963 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
964  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
965  ("(%d:%d)cci_prepare error: code(%d), flag(%d) %s", mapped_conn_id, REQ_ID (statement_id), error,
966  flag, DEBUG_STR (sql_stmt)));
967 #endif
968 
969  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
970  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
971  con_handle->used = false;
972 
973  return error;
974 }

977 cci_get_bind_num (int mapped_stmt_id)

979  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;

1042 T_CCI_COL_INFO *
1043 cci_get_result_info (int mapped_stmt_id, T_CCI_CUBRID_STMT * cmd_type, int *num)
1044 {
1045  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1046  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1047  T_CCI_COL_INFO *col_info = NULL;
1048  int error;
1049 
1050 #ifdef CCI_FULL_DEBUG
1051  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d:%d)cci_get_result_info", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id)));
1052 #endif
1053 
1054  if (cmd_type)
1055  {
1056  *cmd_type = (T_CCI_CUBRID_STMT) (-1);
1057  }
1058 
1059  if (num)
1060  {
1061  *num = 0;
1062  }
1063 
1064  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1065  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1066  {
1067  return NULL;
1068  }
1069 
1070  if (cmd_type)
1071  {
1072  *cmd_type = req_handle->stmt_type;
1073  }
1074 
1075  switch (req_handle->handle_type)
1076  {
1077  case HANDLE_PREPARE:
1078  if (req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_SELECT || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_GET_STATS
1079  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_EVALUATE || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL
1080  || req_handle->stmt_type == CUBRID_STMT_CALL_SP)
1081  {
1082  if (num)
1083  {
1084  *num = req_handle->num_col_info;
1085  }
1086  col_info = req_handle->col_info;
1087  }
1088  break;
1089  case HANDLE_OID_GET:
1090  case HANDLE_SCHEMA_INFO:
1091  case HANDLE_COL_GET:
1092  if (num)
1093  {
1094  *num = req_handle->num_col_info;
1095  }
1096  col_info = req_handle->col_info;
1097  break;
1098  default:
1099  break;
1100  }
1101 
1102  con_handle->used = false;
1103 
1104  return col_info;
1105 }

1108 cci_bind_param (int mapped_stmt_id, int index, T_CCI_A_TYPE a_type, void *value, T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type, char flag)

1110  int error;
1111  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;

1117  dbg_a_type_str (a_type), value, dbg_u_type_str (u_type), flag));
1118 #endif

1131 }

1160 int
1161 cci_register_out_param_ex (int mapped_stmt_id, int index, T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type)
1162 {
1163  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1164  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1165  int error;
1166 
1167  assert (u_type >= CCI_U_TYPE_FIRST && u_type <= CCI_U_TYPE_LAST);
1168 
1169  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1170  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1171  {
1172  return error;
1173  }
1174 
1175  if (index <= 0 || index > req_handle->num_bind)
1176  {
1177  error = CCI_ER_BIND_INDEX;
1178  }
1179  else
1180  {
1181  if (is_connected_to_oracle (con_handle))
1182  {
1183  req_handle->bind_value[index - 1].u_type = u_type;
1184  }
1185 
1186  req_handle->bind_mode[index - 1] |= CCI_PARAM_MODE_OUT;
1187  }
1188 
1189  con_handle->used = false;
1190 
1191  return error;
1192 }

1219 int
1220 cci_bind_param_array (int mapped_stmt_id, int index, T_CCI_A_TYPE a_type, void *value, int *null_ind,
1221  T_CCI_U_TYPE u_type)
1222 {
1223  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1224  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1225  int error = 0;
1226 
1227 #ifdef CCI_FULL_DEBUG
1228  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
1229  ("(%d:%d)cci_bind_param_array: %d %s %p %p %s", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id),
1230  index, dbg_a_type_str (a_type), value, null_ind, dbg_u_type_str (u_type)));
1231 #endif
1232 
1233  assert (u_type >= CCI_U_TYPE_FIRST && u_type <= CCI_U_TYPE_LAST);
1234 
1235  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1236  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1237  {
1238  return error;
1239  }
1240 
1241  if (req_handle->bind_array_size <= 0)
1242  {
1243  error = CCI_ER_BIND_ARRAY_SIZE;
1244  }
1245  else if (index <= 0 || index > req_handle->num_bind)
1246  {
1247  error = CCI_ER_BIND_INDEX;
1248  }
1249  else
1250  {
1251  index--;
1252  req_handle->bind_value[index].u_type = u_type;
1253  req_handle->bind_value[index].size = a_type;
1254  req_handle->bind_value[index].value = value;
1255  req_handle->bind_value[index].null_ind = null_ind;
1256  req_handle->bind_value[index].flag = BIND_PTR_STATIC;
1257  }
1258 
1259  con_handle->used = false;
1260 
1261  return error;
1262 }
1263 
1264 /*
1265  * For the purpose of re-balancing existing connections, cci_prepare,
1266  * cci_execute, cci_execute_array, cci_prepare_and_execute,
1267  * cci_execute_batch require to forcefully disconnect the current
1268  * con_handle when it is in the OUT_TRAN state and the time elapsed
1269  * after the last failure of a host is over rc_time.
1270  */
1271 int
1272 cci_execute (int mapped_stmt_id, char flag, int max_col_size, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1273 {
1274  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1275  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1276  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1277  struct timeval st, et;
1278  bool is_first_exec_in_tran = false;
1279  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
1280  int loop;
1281  char prepare_flag;
1282 
1283 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1284  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
1285  ("(%d:%d)exe: %d, %d", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id), flag, max_col_size));
1286 #endif
1287 
1288  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1289  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1290  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1291  {
1292  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1293  return error;
1294  }
1295  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1296  con_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1297  req_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1298 
1299  if (con_handle->log_slow_queries)
1300  {
1301  gettimeofday (&st, NULL);
1302  }
1303 
1304  API_SLOG (con_handle);
1305  if (con_handle->log_trace_api)
1306  {
1307  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger, "FLAG[%d], MAX_COL_SIZE[%d]", flag, max_col_size);
1308  }
1309 
1310  if (flag & CCI_EXEC_ONLY_QUERY_PLAN)
1311  {
1312  flag |= CCI_EXEC_QUERY_INFO;
1313  }
1314 
1315  /* Asynchronous mode is unsupported. */
1316  if (flag & CCI_EXEC_ASYNC)
1317  {
1318  flag &= ~CCI_EXEC_ASYNC; /* to make it sure */
1319  }
1320 
1321  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_FORCE_FAILBACK (con_handle) && !IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
1322  {
1323  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
1324  }
1325  SET_START_TIME_FOR_QUERY (con_handle, req_handle);
1326 
1327  if (IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle) && req_handle->valid == false)
1328  {
1329  error =
1330  qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, req_handle->prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1331  }
1332 
1333  is_first_exec_in_tran = IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle);
1334 
1335  if (error >= 0)
1336  {
1337  error = qe_execute (req_handle, con_handle, flag, max_col_size, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1338  }
1339  while ((IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) || is_first_exec_in_tran)
1340  && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
1341  {
1342  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
1343  {
1344  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
1345  error = reset_connect (con_handle, req_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1346  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1347  {
1348  break;
1349  }
1350  }
1351 
1352  error =
1353  qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, req_handle->prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1354  if (error < 0)
1355  {
1356  continue;
1357  }
1358 
1359  error = qe_execute (req_handle, con_handle, flag, max_col_size, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1360  }
1361 
1362  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
1363  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V7))
1364  {
1365  loop = 0; /* retry once more */
1366  prepare_flag = (req_handle->prepare_flag | CCI_PREPARE_XASL_CACHE_PINNED);
1367  }
1368  else
1369  {
1370  /* legacy broker */
1371 
1372  loop = 1; /* infinitely */
1373  prepare_flag = req_handle->prepare_flag;
1374  }
1375 
1376  do
1377  {
1378  /* If prepared plan is invalidated while using plan cache, the error, CAS_ER_STMT_POOLING, is returned. In this
1379  * case, prepare and execute have to be executed again. */
1380  if (error == CAS_ER_STMT_POOLING && IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle))
1381  {
1382  req_handle_content_free (req_handle, 1);
1383  error = qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1384  if (error < 0)
1385  {
1386  goto execute_end;
1387  }
1388  error = qe_execute (req_handle, con_handle, flag, max_col_size, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1389  }
1390  }
1391  while (loop && error == CAS_ER_STMT_POOLING && IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle));
1392 
1393 execute_end:
1394  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
1395 
1396  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout)
1397  {
1398  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
1399  }
1400 
1401  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
1402  {
1403  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
1404  }
1405 
1406  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
1407  if (con_handle->log_slow_queries)
1408  {
1409  long elapsed;
1410 
1411  gettimeofday (&et, NULL);
1412  elapsed = ELAPSED_MSECS (et, st);
1413  if (elapsed > con_handle->slow_query_threshold_millis)
1414  {
1415  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger,
1416  "[CONHANDLE - %04d] " "[CAS INFO - %d.%d.%d.%d:%d, %d, %d] "
1417  "[SLOW QUERY - ELAPSED : %d] [SQL - %s]", con_handle->id, con_handle->ip_addr[0],
1418  con_handle->ip_addr[1], con_handle->ip_addr[2], con_handle->ip_addr[3], con_handle->port,
1419  con_handle->cas_id, con_handle->cas_pid, elapsed, req_handle->sql_text);
1420  }
1421  }
1422 
1423  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1424  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1425  con_handle->used = false;
1426 
1427  return error;
1428 }
1429 
1430 /*
1431  * For the purpose of re-balancing existing connections, cci_prepare,
1432  * cci_execute, cci_execute_array, cci_prepare_and_execute,
1433  * cci_execute_batch require to forcefully disconnect the current
1434  * con_handle when it is in the OUT_TRAN state and the time elapsed
1435  * after the last failure of a host is over rc_time.
1436  */
1437 int
1438 cci_prepare_and_execute (int mapped_conn_id, char *sql_stmt, int max_col_size, int *exec_retval, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1439 {
1440  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1441  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1442  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1443  int statement_id;
1444  struct timeval st, et;
1445  int is_first_prepare_in_tran;
1446 
1447 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1448  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
1449  ("cci_prepare_and_execute %d %d %d %d %s", con_handle, max_col_size, DEBUG_STR (sql_stmt)));
1450 #endif
1451 
1452  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1453  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
1454  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1455  {
1456  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1457  if (exec_retval != NULL)
1458  {
1459  *exec_retval = error;
1460  }
1461  return error;
1462  }
1463  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1464  con_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1465 
1466  if (sql_stmt == NULL)
1467  {
1468  error = CCI_ER_STRING_PARAM;
1469  goto error;
1470  }
1471 
1472  if (con_handle->log_slow_queries)
1473  {
1474  gettimeofday (&st, NULL);
1475  }
1476 
1477  API_SLOG (con_handle);
1478  if (con_handle->log_trace_api)
1479  {
1480  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger, "MAX_COL_SIZE[%d], SQL[%s]", max_col_size, sql_stmt);
1481  }
1482 
1483  statement_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
1484  if (statement_id < 0)
1485  {
1486  error = statement_id;
1487  goto prepare_execute_error;
1488  }
1489  req_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1490 
1491  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_FORCE_FAILBACK (con_handle) && !IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
1492  {
1493  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
1494  }
1495 
1496  SET_START_TIME_FOR_QUERY (con_handle, req_handle);
1497  is_first_prepare_in_tran = IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle);
1498 
1499  error = qe_prepare_and_execute (req_handle, con_handle, sql_stmt, max_col_size, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1500  while ((IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) || is_first_prepare_in_tran)
1501  && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
1502  {
1503  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
1504  {
1505  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
1506  error = reset_connect (con_handle, req_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1507  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1508  {
1509  break;
1510  }
1511  }
1512 
1513  error = qe_prepare_and_execute (req_handle, con_handle, sql_stmt, max_col_size, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1514  }
1515 
1516  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
1517  if (error < 0)
1518  {
1519  goto prepare_execute_error;
1520  }
1521 
1522  if (exec_retval != NULL)
1523  {
1524  *exec_retval = error;
1525  }
1526 
1527  if (con_handle->log_slow_queries)
1528  {
1529  long elapsed;
1530 
1531  gettimeofday (&et, NULL);
1532  elapsed = ELAPSED_MSECS (et, st);
1533  if (elapsed > con_handle->slow_query_threshold_millis)
1534  {
1535  CCI_LOGF_DEBUG (con_handle->logger,
1536  "[CONHANDLE - %04d] " "[CAS INFO - %d.%d.%d.%d:%d, %d, %d] "
1537  "[SLOW QUERY - ELAPSED : %d] [SQL - %s]", con_handle->id, con_handle->ip_addr[0],
1538  con_handle->ip_addr[1], con_handle->ip_addr[2], con_handle->ip_addr[3], con_handle->port,
1539  con_handle->cas_id, con_handle->cas_pid, elapsed, req_handle->sql_text);
1540  }
1541  }
1542 
1543  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
1544 
1545  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
1546  {
1547  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
1548  }
1549 
1550  map_open_ots (statement_id, &req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
1551  con_handle->used = false;
1552 
1553  return req_handle->mapped_stmt_id;
1554 
1555 prepare_execute_error:
1556  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
1557 
1558  if (req_handle)
1559  {
1560  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
1561  req_handle = NULL;
1562  }
1563 
1564  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout)
1565  {
1566  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
1567  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
1568  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
1569  }
1570 
1571  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
1572  {
1573  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
1574  }
1575 
1576 error:
1577  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1578  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1579  con_handle->used = false;
1580  if (exec_retval != NULL)
1581  {
1582  *exec_retval = error;
1583  }
1584 
1585  return error;
1586 }
1587 
1588 int
1589 cci_next_result (int mapped_stmt_id, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1590 {
1591  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1592  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1593  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1594 
1595 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1596  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d:%d)cci_next_result", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id)));
1597 #endif
1598 
1599  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1600  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1601  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1602  {
1603  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1604  return error;
1605  }
1606  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1607 
1608  if (req_handle->current_query_res + 1 < req_handle->num_query_res)
1609  {
1610  error = next_result_cmd (req_handle, con_handle, CCI_CLOSE_CURRENT_RESULT, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1611  if (error >= 0)
1612  {
1613  req_handle->current_query_res++;
1614  }
1615  }
1616  else
1617  {
1618  error = CAS_ER_NO_MORE_RESULT_SET;
1619  }
1620 
1621  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1622  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1623  con_handle->used = false;
1624 
1625  return error;
1626 }
1627 
1628 /*
1629  * For the purpose of re-balancing existing connections, cci_prepare,
1630  * cci_execute, cci_execute_array, cci_prepare_and_execute,
1631  * cci_execute_batch require to forcefully disconnect the current
1632  * con_handle when it is in the OUT_TRAN state and the time elapsed
1633  * after the last failure of a host is over rc_time.
1634  */
1635 int
1636 cci_execute_array (int mapped_stmt_id, T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT ** qr, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1637 {
1638  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
1639  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1640  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1641  bool is_first_exec_in_tran = false;
1642  T_BROKER_VERSION broker_ver;
1643  int loop;
1644  char prepare_flag;
1645 
1646 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1647  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d:%d)cci_execute_array", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id)));
1648 #endif
1649 
1650  if (qr == NULL)
1651  {
1652  return CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
1653  }
1654 
1655  *qr = NULL;
1656 
1657  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1658  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
1659  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1660  {
1661  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1662  return error;
1663  }
1664  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1665  con_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1666  req_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
1667 
1668  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_FORCE_FAILBACK (con_handle) && !IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
1669  {
1670  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
1671  }
1672  SET_START_TIME_FOR_QUERY (con_handle, req_handle);
1673 
1674  if (IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle) && req_handle->valid == false)
1675  {
1676  error =
1677  qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, req_handle->prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1678  }
1679 
1680  is_first_exec_in_tran = IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle);
1681 
1682  if (error >= 0)
1683  {
1684  error = qe_execute_array (req_handle, con_handle, qr, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1685  }
1686  while ((IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) || is_first_exec_in_tran)
1687  && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
1688  {
1689  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
1690  {
1691  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
1692  error = reset_connect (con_handle, req_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1693  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1694  {
1695  break;
1696  }
1697  }
1698 
1699  error =
1700  qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, req_handle->prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1701  if (error < 0)
1702  {
1703  continue;
1704  }
1705 
1706  error = qe_execute_array (req_handle, con_handle, qr, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1707  }
1708 
1709  broker_ver = hm_get_broker_version (con_handle);
1710  if (hm_broker_understand_the_protocol (broker_ver, PROTOCOL_V7))
1711  {
1712  loop = 0; /* retry once more */
1713  prepare_flag = (req_handle->prepare_flag | CCI_PREPARE_XASL_CACHE_PINNED);
1714  }
1715  else
1716  {
1717  /* legacy broker */
1718 
1719  loop = 1; /* infinitely */
1720  prepare_flag = req_handle->prepare_flag;
1721  }
1722 
1723  do
1724  {
1725  if (error == CAS_ER_STMT_POOLING && IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle))
1726  {
1727  req_handle_content_free (req_handle, 1);
1728  error = qe_prepare (req_handle, con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, prepare_flag, &(con_handle->err_buf), 1);
1729  if (error < 0)
1730  {
1731  goto execute_end;
1732  }
1733  error = qe_execute_array (req_handle, con_handle, qr, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1734  }
1735  }
1736  while (loop && error == CAS_ER_STMT_POOLING && IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle));
1737 
1738 execute_end:
1739  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
1740 
1741  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout)
1742  {
1743  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
1744  }
1745 
1746  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
1747  {
1748  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
1749  }
1750 
1751  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1752  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1753  con_handle->used = false;
1754 
1755  return error;
1756 }
1757 
1758 int
1759 cci_get_db_parameter (int mapped_conn_id, T_CCI_DB_PARAM param_name, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1760 {
1761  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1762  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1763 
1764 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1765  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_get_db_parameter %d %s", mapped_conn_id, dbg_db_param_str (param_name)));
1766 #endif
1767 
1768  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1769  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
1770  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1771  {
1772  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1773  return error;
1774  }
1775  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1776 
1777  if (param_name < CCI_PARAM_FIRST || param_name > CCI_PARAM_LAST)
1778  {
1779  error = CCI_ER_PARAM_NAME;
1780  goto ret;
1781  }
1782 
1783  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_ISOLATION_LEVEL && con_handle->isolation_level != TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION)
1784  {
1785  memcpy (value, &con_handle->isolation_level, sizeof (int));
1786  goto ret;
1787  }
1788 
1789  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_LOCK_TIMEOUT && con_handle->lock_timeout != CCI_LOCK_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT)
1790  {
1791  memcpy (value, &con_handle->lock_timeout, sizeof (int));
1792  goto ret;
1793  }
1794 
1795  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_AUTO_COMMIT)
1796  {
1797  memcpy (value, &con_handle->autocommit_mode, sizeof (int));
1798  goto ret;
1799  }
1800 
1801  error = qe_get_db_parameter (con_handle, param_name, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1802  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
1803  {
1804  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
1805  {
1806  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
1807  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1808  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1809  {
1810  break;
1811  }
1812  }
1813 
1814  error = qe_get_db_parameter (con_handle, param_name, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1815  }
1816 
1817 ret:
1818  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1819  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1820  con_handle->used = false;
1821 
1822  return error;
1823 }
1824 
1825 long
1826 cci_escape_string (int mapped_conn_id, char *to, const char *from, unsigned long length, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1827 {
1828  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1829  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1830  unsigned long i;
1831  char *target_ptr = to;
1832  int no_backslash_escapes;
1833 
1834 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1835  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_escape_string %d", mapped_conn_id));
1836 #endif
1837  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1838  if (to == NULL || from == NULL)
1839  {
1840  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS, NULL);
1841  return CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
1842  }
1843 
1844  if (mapped_conn_id == CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_FALSE || mapped_conn_id == CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_TRUE)
1845  {
1846  no_backslash_escapes = mapped_conn_id;
1847  goto convert;
1848  }
1849 
1850  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
1851  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1852  {
1853  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1854  return error;
1855  }
1856  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1857 
1858  if (con_handle->no_backslash_escapes == CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_NOT_SET)
1859  {
1860  error =
1861  qe_get_db_parameter (con_handle, CCI_PARAM_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES, &con_handle->no_backslash_escapes,
1862  &(con_handle->err_buf));
1863  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
1864  {
1865  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
1866  {
1867  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
1868  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
1869  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1870  {
1871  break;
1872  }
1873  }
1874 
1875  error =
1876  qe_get_db_parameter (con_handle, CCI_PARAM_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES, &con_handle->no_backslash_escapes,
1877  &(con_handle->err_buf));
1878  }
1879 
1880  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1881  {
1882  goto error;
1883  }
1884  }
1885 
1886  no_backslash_escapes = con_handle->no_backslash_escapes;
1887 
1888 convert:
1889  for (i = 0; i < length; i++)
1890  {
1891  if (from[i] == '\'')
1892  {
1893  /* single-quote is converted to two-single-quote */
1894  *(target_ptr) = '\'';
1895  *(target_ptr + 1) = '\'';
1896  target_ptr += 2;
1897  }
1898  else if (no_backslash_escapes == CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_FALSE)
1899  {
1900  if (from[i] == '\0')
1901  {
1902  /* ASCII 0 is converted to "\" + "0" */
1903  *(target_ptr) = '\\';
1904  *(target_ptr + 1) = '0';
1905  target_ptr += 2;
1906  }
1907  else if (from[i] == '\r')
1908  {
1909  /* carrage return is converted to "\" + "r" */
1910  *(target_ptr) = '\\';
1911  *(target_ptr + 1) = 'r';
1912  target_ptr += 2;
1913  }
1914  else if (from[i] == '\n')
1915  {
1916  /* new line is converted to "\" + "n" */
1917  *(target_ptr) = '\\';
1918  *(target_ptr + 1) = 'n';
1919  target_ptr += 2;
1920  }
1921  else if (from[i] == '\\')
1922  {
1923  /* \ is converted to \\ */
1924  *(target_ptr) = '\\';
1925  *(target_ptr + 1) = '\\';
1926  target_ptr += 2;
1927  }
1928  else
1929  {
1930  *(target_ptr) = from[i];
1931  target_ptr++;
1932  }
1933  }
1934  else
1935  {
1936  *(target_ptr) = from[i];
1937  target_ptr++;
1938  }
1939  }
1940 
1941  /* terminating NULL char */
1942  *target_ptr = '\0';
1943 
1944  if (con_handle != NULL)
1945  {
1946  assert (mapped_conn_id != CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_FALSE && mapped_conn_id != CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_TRUE);
1947  con_handle->used = false;
1948  }
1949 
1950  return ((long) (target_ptr - to));
1951 
1952 error:
1953  assert (con_handle != NULL);
1954  assert (mapped_conn_id != CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_FALSE && mapped_conn_id != CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_TRUE);
1955 
1956  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
1957  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
1958  con_handle->used = false;
1959 
1960  return ((long) error);
1961 }
1962 
1963 int
1964 cci_set_db_parameter (int mapped_conn_id, T_CCI_DB_PARAM param_name, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
1965 {
1966  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
1967  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
1968  int i_val;
1969 
1970 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
1971  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_set_db_parameter %d %s", mapped_conn_id, dbg_db_param_str (param_name)));
1972 #endif
1973 
1974  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
1975  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
1976  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
1977  {
1978  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
1979  return error;
1980  }
1981  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
1982 
1983  if (param_name < CCI_PARAM_FIRST || param_name > CCI_PARAM_LAST)
1984  {
1985  error = CCI_ER_PARAM_NAME;
1986  goto ret;
1987  }
1988 
1989  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_ISOLATION_LEVEL && con_handle->isolation_level != TRAN_UNKNOWN_ISOLATION
1990  && con_handle->isolation_level == *((int *) value))
1991  {
1992  goto ret;
1993  }
1994 
1995  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_LOCK_TIMEOUT && con_handle->lock_timeout != CCI_LOCK_TIMEOUT_DEFAULT
1996  && con_handle->lock_timeout == *((int *) value))
1997  {
1998  goto ret;
1999  }
2000 
2001  error = qe_set_db_parameter (con_handle, param_name, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2002  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
2003  {
2004  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
2005  {
2006  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
2007  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2008  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2009  {
2010  break;
2011  }
2012  }
2013 
2014  error = qe_set_db_parameter (con_handle, param_name, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2015  }
2016 
2017  if (error >= 0)
2018  {
2019  i_val = *((int *) value);
2020 
2021  if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_LOCK_TIMEOUT)
2022  {
2023  con_handle->lock_timeout = i_val;
2024  }
2025  else if (param_name == CCI_PARAM_ISOLATION_LEVEL)
2026  {
2027  con_handle->isolation_level = (T_CCI_TRAN_ISOLATION) i_val;
2028  }
2029  }
2030 
2031 ret:
2032  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
2033  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
2034  con_handle->used = false;
2035 
2036  return error;
2037 }

2039 static int
2040 convert_cas_mode_to_driver_mode (int cas_mode)
2041 {
2042  int driver_mode = 0;
2043 
2044  switch (cas_mode)
2045  {
2046  case CAS_CHANGE_MODE_AUTO:
2047  driver_mode = CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_AUTO;
2048  break;
2049  case CAS_CHANGE_MODE_KEEP:
2050  driver_mode = CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_KEEP;
2051  break;
2052  default:
2053  driver_mode = CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_UNKNOWN;
2054  break;
2055  }
2056 
2057  return driver_mode;
2058 }
2059 
2060 static int
2061 convert_driver_mode_to_cas_mode (int driver_mode)
2062 {
2063  int cas_mode = 0;
2064 
2065  switch (driver_mode)
2066  {
2067  case CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_AUTO:
2068  cas_mode = CAS_CHANGE_MODE_AUTO;
2069  break;
2070  case CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_KEEP:
2071  cas_mode = CAS_CHANGE_MODE_KEEP;
2072  break;
2073  default:
2074  cas_mode = CAS_CHANGE_MODE_UNKNOWN;
2075  break;
2076  }
2077 
2078  return cas_mode;
2079 }

2081 int
2082 cci_set_cas_change_mode (int mapped_conn_id, int driver_mode, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2083 {
2084  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
2085  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2086  int r, cas_mode;
2087 
2088 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
2089  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_set_cas_change_mode %d %d", mapped_conn_id, driver_mode));
2090 #endif
2091 
2092  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
2093  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
2094  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2095  {
2096  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
2097  return error;
2098  }
2099  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
2100 
2101  cas_mode = convert_driver_mode_to_cas_mode (driver_mode);
2102  if (cas_mode == CAS_CHANGE_MODE_UNKNOWN)
2103  {
2104  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
2105  goto ret;
2106  }
2107 
2108  r = qe_set_cas_change_mode (con_handle, cas_mode, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2109  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (r, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
2110  {
2111  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, r))
2112  {
2113  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
2114  r = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2115  if (r != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2116  {
2117  break;
2118  }
2119  }
2120 
2121  r = qe_set_cas_change_mode (con_handle, cas_mode, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2122  }
2123 
2124  if (r < 0)
2125  {
2126  error = r;
2127  }
2128  else
2129  {
2130  driver_mode = convert_cas_mode_to_driver_mode (r);
2131  if (driver_mode == CCI_CAS_CHANGE_MODE_UNKNOWN)
2132  {
2133  error = CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION;
2134  }
2135  }
2136 
2137 ret:
2138  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
2139  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
2140  con_handle->used = false;
2141 
2142  if (error < 0)
2143  {
2144  return error;
2145  }
2146  else
2147  {
2148  return driver_mode;
2149  }
2150 }

2193 int
2194 cci_close_req_handle (int mapped_stmt_id)
2195 {
2196  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
2197  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
2198  int error = 0;
2199 
2200 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
2201  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d:%d)cci_close_req_handle", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id)));
2202 #endif
2203 
2204  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
2205  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2206  {
2207  return error;
2208  }
2209  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
2210 
2211  API_SLOG (con_handle);
2212 
2213  if (DOES_CONNECTION_HAVE_STMT_POOL (con_handle) && req_handle->sql_text != NULL)
2214  {
2215  qe_close_query_result (req_handle, con_handle);
2216 
2217  /* free req_handle resources */
2218  req_handle_content_free_for_pool (req_handle);
2219 
2220  if (con_handle->autocommit_mode == CCI_AUTOCOMMIT_TRUE && IS_IN_TRAN (con_handle))
2221  {
2222  T_CCI_ERROR err_buf;
2223  qe_end_tran (con_handle, CCI_TRAN_ROLLBACK, &err_buf);
2224  }
2225 
2226  error = hm_req_add_to_pool (con_handle, req_handle->sql_text, mapped_stmt_id, req_handle);
2227  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2228  {
2229  goto cci_close_req_handle_end;
2230  }
2231  }
2232 
2233  if (req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_PREPARE || req_handle->handle_type == HANDLE_SCHEMA_INFO)
2234  {
2235  error = qe_close_req_handle (req_handle, con_handle);
2236  if (IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
2237  {
2238  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
2239  {
2240  error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2241  }
2242  }
2243  }
2244  else
2245  {
2246  error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2247  }
2248  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
2249  req_handle = NULL;
2250 
2251  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
2252  {
2253  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
2254  }
2255 
2256 cci_close_req_handle_end:
2257  API_ELOG (con_handle, error);
2258  con_handle->used = false;
2259  hm_release_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
2260 
2261  return error;
2262 }

2373 static int
2374 cci_schema_info_internal (int mapped_conn_id, T_CCI_SCH_TYPE type, char *arg1, char *arg2, char flag, int shard_id,
2375  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2376 {
2377  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
2378  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
2379  int statement_id = -1;
2380  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2381 
2382 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
2383  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
2384  ("cci_schema_info %d %s %s %s %d", mapped_conn_id, dbg_sch_type_str (type), DEBUG_STR (arg1),
2385  DEBUG_STR (arg2), flag));
2386 #endif
2387 
2388  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
2389  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
2390  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2391  {
2392  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
2393  return error;
2394  }
2395  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
2396 
2397  statement_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
2398  if (statement_id < 0)
2399  {
2400  error = statement_id;
2401  goto ret;
2402  }
2403 
2404  error = qe_schema_info (req_handle, con_handle, (int) type, arg1, arg2, flag, shard_id, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2405  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
2406  {
2407  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
2408  {
2409  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
2410  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2411  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2412  {
2413  break;
2414  }
2415  }
2416 
2417  error = qe_schema_info (req_handle, con_handle, (int) type, arg1, arg2, flag, shard_id, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2418  }
2419 
2420  if (error < 0)
2421  {
2422  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
2423  req_handle = NULL;
2424  }
2425 
2426 ret:
2427  con_handle->used = false;
2428 
2429  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2430  {
2431  map_open_ots (statement_id, &req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
2432  return req_handle->mapped_stmt_id;
2433  }
2434 
2435  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
2436  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
2437 
2438  return error;
2439 }

2515 int
2516 cci_oid_get (int mapped_conn_id, char *oid_str, char **attr_name, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
2517 {
2518  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
2519  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
2520  int statement_id = -1;
2521  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
2522 
2523 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
2524  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("cci_oid_get %d", mapped_conn_id));
2525 #endif
2526 
2527  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
2528  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
2529  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2530  {
2531  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
2532  return error;
2533  }
2534  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
2535 
2536  error = 0;
2537 
2538  statement_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
2539  if (statement_id < 0)
2540  {
2541  error = statement_id;
2542  goto ret;
2543  }
2544 
2545  error = qe_oid_get (req_handle, con_handle, oid_str, attr_name, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2546  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
2547  {
2548  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
2549  {
2550  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
2551  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2552  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2553  {
2554  break;
2555  }
2556  }
2557 
2558  error = qe_oid_get (req_handle, con_handle, oid_str, attr_name, &(con_handle->err_buf));
2559  }
2560 
2561  if (error < 0)
2562  {
2563  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
2564  req_handle = NULL;
2565  }
2566 
2567 ret:
2568  con_handle->used = false;
2569 
2570  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
2571  {
2572  map_open_ots (statement_id, &req_handle->mapped_stmt_id);
2573  return req_handle->mapped_stmt_id;
2574  }
2575 
2576  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
2577  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
2578 
2579  return error;
2580 }

3132 int
3133 cci_cursor_update (int mapped_stmt_id, int cursor_pos, int index, T_CCI_A_TYPE a_type, void *value,
3134  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
3135 {
3136  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
3137  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
3138  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
3139 
3140 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
3141  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg
3142  ("(%d:%d)cci_cursor_update: %d %d %s %p", CON_ID (mapped_stmt_id), REQ_ID (mapped_stmt_id),
3143  cursor_pos, index, dbg_a_type_str (a_type), value));
3144 #endif
3145 
3146  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
3147  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
3148  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3149  {
3150  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
3151  return error;
3152  }
3153  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
3154 
3155  if ((req_handle->prepare_flag & CCI_PREPARE_UPDATABLE) == 0)
3156  {
3157  error = CCI_ER_NOT_UPDATABLE;
3158  }
3159  else
3160  {
3161  error = qe_cursor_update (req_handle, con_handle, cursor_pos, index, a_type, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3162  }
3163 
3164  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
3165  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
3166  con_handle->used = false;
3167 
3168  return error;
3169 }
3170 
3171 /*
3172  * For the purpose of re-balancing existing connections, cci_prepare,
3173  * cci_execute, cci_execute_array, cci_prepare_and_execute,
3174  * cci_execute_batch require to forcefully disconnect the current
3175  * con_handle when it is in the OUT_TRAN state and the time elapsed
3176  * after the last failure of a host is over rc_time.
3177  */
3178 int
3179 cci_execute_batch (int mapped_conn_id, int num_query, char **sql_stmt, T_CCI_QUERY_RESULT ** qr, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
3180 {
3181  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
3182  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
3183 
3184 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
3185  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)cci_execute_batch: %d", mapped_conn_id, num_query));
3186 #endif
3187 
3188  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
3189  if (qr == NULL || sql_stmt == NULL)
3190  {
3191  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS, NULL);
3192  return CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
3193  }
3194 
3195  *qr = NULL;
3196  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
3197  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3198  {
3199  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
3200  return error;
3201  }
3202  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
3203  con_handle->shard_id = CCI_SHARD_ID_INVALID;
3204 
3205  if (num_query <= 0)
3206  {
3207  goto ret;
3208  }
3209 
3210  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_FORCE_FAILBACK (con_handle) && !IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
3211  {
3212  hm_force_close_connection (con_handle);
3213  }
3214  SET_START_TIME_FOR_QUERY (con_handle, NULL);
3215 
3216  error = qe_execute_batch (con_handle, num_query, sql_stmt, qr, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3217  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
3218  {
3219  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
3220  {
3221  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
3222  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3223  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3224  {
3225  break;
3226  }
3227  }
3228 
3229  error = qe_execute_batch (con_handle, num_query, sql_stmt, qr, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3230  }
3231 
3232  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT && con_handle->disconnect_on_query_timeout)
3233  {
3234  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
3235  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
3236  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
3237  }
3238 
3239  RESET_START_TIME (con_handle);
3240 
3241 ret:
3242  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
3243  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
3244  con_handle->used = false;
3245 
3246  return error;
3247 }

3268

3706 cci_lob_new (int mapped_conn_id, void *lob, T_CCI_U_TYPE type, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)

3714  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3715  {
3716  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
3717  return error;
3718  }
3719  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
3720 
3721  if (lob == NULL)
3722  {
3723  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_LOB_HANDLE;
3724  goto ret;
3725  }
3726 
3727  error = qe_lob_new (con_handle, &lob_handle, type, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3728  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
3729  {
3730  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
3731  {
3732  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
3733  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3734  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3735  {
3736  break;
3737  }
3738  }
3739 
3740  error = qe_lob_new (con_handle, &lob_handle, type, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3741  }
3742 
3743  if (error < 0)
3744  {
3745  goto ret;
3746  }
3747 
3748  if (type == CCI_U_TYPE_BLOB)
3749  {
3750  *(T_CCI_BLOB *) lob = (T_CCI_BLOB) lob_handle;
3751  }
3752  else if (type == CCI_U_TYPE_CLOB)
3753  {
3754  *(T_CCI_CLOB *) lob = (T_CCI_CLOB) lob_handle;
3755  }
3756  else
3757  {
3758  *(T_CCI_CLOB *) lob = NULL;
3759  }
3760 
3761 ret:
3762  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
3763  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
3764  con_handle->used = false;
3765 
3766  return error;
3767 }

3820 static int
3821 cci_lob_write (int mapped_conn_id, void *lob, long long start_pos, int length, const char *buf, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
3822 {
3823  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
3824  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
3825  T_LOB *lob_handle = (T_LOB *) lob;
3826  int nwritten = 0;
3827  int current_write_len;
3828 
3829  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
3830  if (buf == NULL)
3831  {
3832  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS, NULL);
3833  return CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
3834  }
3835 
3836  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
3837  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3838  {
3839  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
3840  return error;
3841  }
3842  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
3843 
3844  if (lob == NULL)
3845  {
3846  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_LOB_HANDLE;
3847  goto ret;
3848  }
3849 
3850  if (IS_OUT_TRAN_STATUS (con_handle))
3851  {
3852  error = cas_connect (con_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3853  }
3854 
3855  if (error >= 0)
3856  {
3857  while (nwritten < length)
3858  {
3859  current_write_len = ((LOB_IO_LENGTH > length - nwritten) ? (length - nwritten) : LOB_IO_LENGTH);
3860  error =
3861  qe_lob_write (con_handle, lob_handle, start_pos + nwritten, current_write_len, buf + nwritten,
3862  &(con_handle->err_buf));
3863  if (error >= 0)
3864  {
3865  nwritten += error;
3866  }
3867  else
3868  {
3869  break;
3870  }
3871  }
3872  }
3873 
3874 ret:
3875  con_handle->used = false;
3876 
3877  if (error >= 0)
3878  {
3879  return nwritten;
3880  }
3881 
3882  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
3883  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
3884 
3885  return error;
3886 }

3894  ("(%d)cci_blob_write: lob %p pos %d len %d", mapped_conn_id, blob, start_pos, length));
3895 #endif
3896 
3897  return cci_lob_write (mapped_conn_id, blob, start_pos, length, buf, err_buf);
3898 }

3912 static int
3913 cci_lob_read (int mapped_conn_id, void *lob, long long start_pos, int length, char *buf, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
3914 {
3915  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
3916  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
3917  T_LOB *lob_handle = (T_LOB *) lob;
3918  int nread = 0;
3919  int current_read_len;
3920  INT64 lob_size;
3921 
3922  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
3923  if (buf == NULL)
3924  {
3925  set_error_buffer (err_buf, CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS, NULL);
3926  return CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
3927  }
3928 
3929  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
3930  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
3931  {
3932  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
3933  return error;
3934  }
3935  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
3936 
3937  if (lob == NULL)
3938  {
3939  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_LOB_HANDLE;
3940  goto ret;
3941  }
3942 
3943  if (IS_OUT_TRAN_STATUS (con_handle))
3944  {
3945  error = cas_connect (con_handle, &(con_handle->err_buf));
3946  }
3947 
3948  lob_size = t_lob_get_size (lob_handle->handle);
3949 
3950  if (start_pos >= lob_size)
3951  {
3952  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_LOB_READ_POS;
3953  }
3954 
3955  if (error >= 0)
3956  {
3957  while (nread < length && start_pos + nread < lob_size)
3958  {
3959  current_read_len = ((LOB_IO_LENGTH > length - nread) ? (length - nread) : LOB_IO_LENGTH);
3960  error =
3961  qe_lob_read (con_handle, lob_handle, start_pos + nread, current_read_len, buf + nread,
3962  &(con_handle->err_buf));
3963  if (error >= 0)
3964  {
3965  nread += error;
3966  }
3967  else
3968  {
3969  break;
3970  }
3971  }
3972  }
3973 
3974 ret:
3975  con_handle->used = false;
3976 
3977  if (error >= 0)
3978  {
3979  return nread;
3980  }
3981 
3982  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
3983  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
3984 
3985  return error;
3986 }

4219 int
4220 cci_row_count (int mapped_conn_id, int *row_count, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4221 {
4222  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4223  int req_handle_id = -1;
4224  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
4225  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
4226 
4227 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
4228  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)cci_row_count", mapped_conn_id));
4229 #endif
4230 
4231  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
4232  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
4233  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4234  {
4235  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4236  return error;
4237  }
4238  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
4239 
4240  req_handle_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
4241  if (req_handle_id < 0)
4242  {
4243  error = req_handle_id;
4244  goto ret;
4245  }
4246 
4247  error = qe_get_row_count (req_handle, con_handle, row_count, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4248  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
4249  {
4250  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
4251  {
4252  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
4253  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4254  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4255  {
4256  break;
4257  }
4258  }
4259 
4260  error = qe_get_row_count (req_handle, con_handle, row_count, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4261  }
4262  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
4263  req_handle = NULL;
4264 
4265 ret:
4266  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
4267  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
4268  con_handle->used = false;
4269 
4270  return error;
4271 }

4295 int
4296 cci_get_shard_id_with_req_handle (int mapped_stmt_id, int *shard_id, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4297 {

4299  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;

4303  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
4304  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)

4310  {
4311  *shard_id = req_handle->shard_id;
4312  }
4313  con_handle->used = false;
4314 
4315  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4316 }
4317 
4318 /*
4319  * IMPORTANT: cci_last_insert_id and cci_get_last_insert_id
4320  *
4321  * cci_get_last_insert_id set value as last insert id in con_handle
4322  * so it could be changed when new insertion is executed.
4323  *
4324  * cci_last_insert_id set value as allocated last insert id
4325  * so it won't be changed but user should free it manually.
4326  *
4327  * But, It's possible to make some problem when it working with
4328  * user own memory allocators or Windows shared library memory space.
4329  *
4330  * So we deprecate cci_last_insert_id and strongly recommend to use
4331  * cci_get_last_insert_id.
4332  */
4333 int
4334 cci_last_insert_id (int mapped_conn_id, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4335 {
4336  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4337  char *ptr, *val;
4338 
4339  /* value init & null check are in below function */
4340  error = cci_get_last_insert_id (mapped_conn_id, &ptr, err_buf);
4341 
4342  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR && ptr != NULL && value != NULL)
4343  {
4344  /* 2 for sign & null termination */
4345  size_t value_len = strnlen (ptr, MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 2);
4346  assert (value_len < MAX_NUMERIC_PRECISION + 2);
4347 
4348  val = (char *) MALLOC (value_len + 1);
4349  if (val == NULL)
4350  {
4351  error = CCI_ER_NO_MORE_MEMORY;
4352  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4353  return error;
4354  }
4355 
4356  strncpy (val, ptr, value_len);
4357  val[value_len] = '\0';
4358 
4359  *(char **) value = val;
4360  }
4361 
4362  return error;
4363 }
4364 
4365 int
4366 cci_get_last_insert_id (int mapped_conn_id, void *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4367 {
4368  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4369  int req_handle_id = -1;
4370  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
4371  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
4372 
4373 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
4374  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)cci_get_last_insert_id", mapped_conn_id));
4375 #endif
4376 
4377  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
4378 
4379  if (value == NULL)
4380  {
4381  error = CCI_ER_INVALID_ARGS;
4382  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4383  return error;
4384  }
4385 
4386  *(char **) value = NULL;
4387 
4388  error = hm_get_connection (mapped_conn_id, &con_handle);
4389  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4390  {
4391  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4392  return error;
4393  }
4394 
4395  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
4396 
4397  req_handle_id = hm_req_handle_alloc (con_handle, &req_handle);
4398  if (req_handle_id < 0)
4399  {
4400  error = req_handle_id;
4401  goto ret;
4402  }
4403  error = qe_get_last_insert_id (req_handle, con_handle, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4404  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
4405  {
4406  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
4407  {
4408  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
4409  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4410  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4411  {
4412  break;
4413  }
4414  }
4415 
4416  error = qe_get_last_insert_id (req_handle, con_handle, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4417  }
4418  hm_req_handle_free (con_handle, req_handle);
4419  req_handle = NULL;
4420 
4421 ret:
4422  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
4423  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
4424  con_handle->used = false;
4425 
4426  return error;
4427 }

4669 /*
4670  Called by PRINT_CCI_ERROR()
4671 */
4672 int
4673 cci_get_error_msg (int error, T_CCI_ERROR * cci_err, char *buf, int bufsize)
4674 {
4675  const char *err_msg;
4676 
4677  if ((buf == NULL) || (bufsize <= 0))
4678  {
4679  return -1;
4680  }
4681 
4682  err_msg = cci_get_err_msg_internal (error);
4683  if (err_msg == NULL)
4684  {
4685  return -1;
4686  }
4687  else
4688  {
4689  if ((error < CCI_ER_DBMS) && (error > CCI_ER_END))
4690  {
4691  snprintf (buf, bufsize, "CCI Error : %s", err_msg);
4692  }
4693  else if ((error < CAS_ER_DBMS) && (error >= CAS_ER_IS))
4694  {
4695  snprintf (buf, bufsize, "CUBRID CAS Error : %s", err_msg);
4696  }
4697  if ((error == CCI_ER_DBMS) || (error == CAS_ER_DBMS))
4698  {
4699  if (cci_err == NULL)
4700  {
4701  snprintf (buf, bufsize, "%s ", err_msg);
4702  }
4703  else
4704  {
4705  snprintf (buf, bufsize, "%s : (%d) %s", err_msg, cci_err->err_code, cci_err->err_msg);
4706  }
4707  }
4708  }
4709 
4710  return 0;
4711 }
4712 
4713 /*
4714  Called by applications.
4715  They don't need prefix such as "ERROR :" or "CUBRID CAS ERROR".
4716  */
4717 int
4718 cci_get_err_msg (int error, char *buf, int bufsize)
4719 {
4720  const char *err_msg;
4721 
4722  if ((buf == NULL) || (bufsize <= 0))
4723  {
4724  return -1;
4725  }
4726 
4727  err_msg = cci_get_err_msg_internal (error);
4728  if (err_msg == NULL)
4729  {
4730  return -1;
4731  }
4732  else
4733  {
4734  snprintf (buf, bufsize, "%s", err_msg);
4735  }
4736 
4737  return 0;
4738 }

4748 static void
4749 reset_error_buffer (T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4750 {
4751  if (err_buf != NULL)
4752  {
4753  err_buf->err_code = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4754  err_buf->err_msg[0] = '\0';
4755  }
4756 }
4757 
4758 static int
4759 col_set_add_drop (int resolved_id, char col_cmd, char *oid_str, char *col_attr, char *value, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4760 {
4761  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4762  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
4763 
4764  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
4765  error = hm_get_connection (resolved_id, &con_handle);
4766  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4767  {
4768  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4769  return error;
4770  }
4771  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
4772 
4773  error = qe_col_set_add_drop (con_handle, col_cmd, oid_str, col_attr, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4774  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
4775  {
4776  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
4777  {
4778  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
4779  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4780  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4781  {
4782  break;
4783  }
4784  }
4785 
4786  error = qe_col_set_add_drop (con_handle, col_cmd, oid_str, col_attr, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4787  }
4788 
4789  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
4790  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
4791  con_handle->used = false;
4792 
4793  return error;
4794 }

4796 static int
4797 col_seq_op (int resolved_id, char col_cmd, char *oid_str, char *col_attr, int index, const char *value,
4798  T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4799 {
4800  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4801  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
4802 
4803  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
4804  error = hm_get_connection (resolved_id, &con_handle);
4805  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4806  {
4807  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4808  return error;
4809  }
4810  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
4811 
4812  error = qe_col_seq_op (con_handle, col_cmd, oid_str, col_attr, index, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4813  while (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle) && IS_ER_TO_RECONNECT (error, con_handle->err_buf.err_code))
4814  {
4815  if (NEED_TO_RECONNECT (con_handle, error))
4816  {
4817  /* Finally, reset_connect will return ER_TIMEOUT */
4818  error = reset_connect (con_handle, NULL, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4819  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4820  {
4821  break;
4822  }
4823  }
4824 
4825  error = qe_col_seq_op (con_handle, col_cmd, oid_str, col_attr, index, value, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4826  }
4827 
4828  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
4829  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
4830  con_handle->used = false;
4831 
4832  return error;
4833 }
4834 
4835 static int
4836 fetch_cmd (int mapped_stmt_id, char flag, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4837 {
4838  T_REQ_HANDLE *req_handle = NULL;
4839  T_CON_HANDLE *con_handle = NULL;
4840  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4841  int result_set_index = 0;
4842 
4843  reset_error_buffer (err_buf);
4844  error = hm_get_statement (mapped_stmt_id, &con_handle, &req_handle);
4845  if (error != CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4846  {
4847  set_error_buffer (err_buf, error, NULL);
4848  return error;
4849  }
4850  reset_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf));
4851 
4852  if ((req_handle->prepare_flag & CCI_PREPARE_HOLDABLE) != 0 && (flag & CCI_FETCH_SENSITIVE) != 0)
4853  {
4854  error = CAS_ER_HOLDABLE_NOT_ALLOWED;
4855  }
4856 
4857  if (error >= 0)
4858  {
4859  error = qe_fetch (req_handle, con_handle, flag, result_set_index, &(con_handle->err_buf));
4860  }
4861 
4862  if (IS_OUT_TRAN (con_handle))
4863  {
4864  hm_check_rc_time (con_handle);
4865  }
4866 
4867  set_error_buffer (&(con_handle->err_buf), error, NULL);
4868  get_last_error (con_handle, err_buf);
4869  con_handle->used = false;
4870 
4871  return error;
4872 }
4873 
4874 static int
4875 cas_connect (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4876 {
4877  int connect;
4878 
4879  return cas_connect_with_ret (con_handle, err_buf, &connect);
4880 }
4881 
4882 static int
4883 cas_connect_with_ret (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf, int *connect)
4884 {
4885  int error;
4886 
4887 #ifdef CCI_DEBUG
4888  CCI_DEBUG_PRINT (print_debug_msg ("(%d)cas_connect_with_ret", con_handle->id));
4889 #endif
4890  error = cas_connect_internal (con_handle, err_buf, connect);
4891 
4892  /* req_handle_table should be managed by list too. */
4893  if (((*connect) != 0) && IS_BROKER_STMT_POOL (con_handle))
4894  {
4895  hm_invalidate_all_req_handle (con_handle);
4896  }
4897  if ((*connect) != 0)
4898  {
4899  con_handle->no_backslash_escapes = CCI_NO_BACKSLASH_ESCAPES_NOT_SET;
4900  }
4901 
4902  return error;
4903 }
4904 
4905 static int
4906 cas_connect_internal (T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf, int *connect)
4907 {
4908  int error = CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4909  int i;
4910  int remained_time = 0;
4911  int retry = 0;
4912 
4913  assert (connect != NULL);
4914 
4915  *connect = 0;
4916 
4917  if (TIMEOUT_IS_SET (con_handle))
4918  {
4919  remained_time = (con_handle->current_timeout - get_elapsed_time (&con_handle->start_time));
4920  if (remained_time <= 0)
4921  {
4922  return CCI_ER_LOGIN_TIMEOUT;
4923  }
4924  }
4925 
4926  if (net_check_cas_request (con_handle) != 0)
4927  {
4928  if (!IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
4929  {
4930  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
4931  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
4932  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
4933  }
4934  }
4935 
4936  if (!IS_INVALID_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd))
4937  {
4938  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4939  }
4940  CLOSE_SOCKET (con_handle->sock_fd);
4941  con_handle->sock_fd = INVALID_SOCKET;
4942  con_handle->con_status = CCI_CON_STATUS_OUT_TRAN;
4943 
4944  if (con_handle->alter_host_count == 0)
4945  {
4946  error = net_connect_srv (con_handle, con_handle->alter_host_id, err_buf, remained_time);
4947  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4948  {
4949  *connect = 1;
4950  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4951  }
4952  }
4953 
4954  do
4955  {
4956  for (i = 0; i < con_handle->alter_host_count; i++)
4957  {
4958  /* if all hosts turn out to be unreachable, ignore host reachability and try one more time */
4959  if (hm_is_host_reachable (con_handle, i) || retry)
4960  {
4961  error = net_connect_srv (con_handle, i, err_buf, remained_time);
4962  if (error == CCI_ER_NO_ERROR)
4963  {
4964  hm_set_host_status (con_handle, i, REACHABLE);
4965 
4966  *connect = 1;
4967  return CCI_ER_NO_ERROR;
4968  }
4969 
4970  if (error == CCI_ER_COMMUNICATION || error == CCI_ER_CONNECT || error == CCI_ER_LOGIN_TIMEOUT
4971  || error == CAS_ER_FREE_SERVER)
4972  {
4973  hm_set_host_status (con_handle, i, UNREACHABLE);
4974  }
4975  else
4976  {
4977  break;
4978  }
4979  }
4980  con_handle->last_failure_time = time (NULL);
4981  }
4982  retry++;
4983  }
4984  while (retry < 2);
4985 
4986  if (error == CCI_ER_QUERY_TIMEOUT)
4987  {
4988  error = CCI_ER_LOGIN_TIMEOUT;
4989  }
4990 
4991  return error;
4992 }
4993 
4994 static int
4995 next_result_cmd (T_REQ_HANDLE * req_handle, T_CON_HANDLE * con_handle, char flag, T_CCI_ERROR * err_buf)
4996 {
4997  return qe_next_result (req_handle, flag, con_handle, err_buf);
4998 }
